  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA296-kiḷavi">itu tōḻiyāṟ pirivuṇarttappaṭṭa talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said who was informed of the separation by the confidante.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA296">
<l>            eṉṉō vatuko ṟōḻi maṉṉar</l>
<l>            viṉaival yāṉaip pukarmukat taṇinta</l>
<l>            poṉce yōṭai puṉainalaṅ kaṭuppap</l>
<l>            puḻaṟkāyk koṉṟaik kōṭaṇi koṭiyiṇa</l>
<l>            rēkaṉ mīmicai mētaka malarum </l>
<l>            pirintō riraṅku marumpeṟaṟ kālaiyum</l>
<l>            viṉaiyē niṉainta vuḷḷamoṭu tuṉaiic</l>
<l>            celpa veṉpa kātala</l>
<l>            roḻitu meṉpanām varuntupaṭa ruḻantē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>What will stop [it], friend?</l>
<l>He will go, they say, [our] lover,</l>
<l>hastening with a mind thinking just of work,</l>
<l rend="indent">even at a time difficult to obtain,</l>
<l rend="indent">when those that are separated are aggrieved,</l>
<l rend="indent2">when eminently on the height of big stones the trailing clusters</l>
<l rend="indent2">blossom, adorning the branches of Laburnum with hollow unripe fruit,</l>
<l rend="indent3">resembling the adornments of golden metal plates</l>
<l rend="indent3">that decorated the spotted face of the elephant strong in work</l>
<l rend="indent3">for the king.</l>
<l>We will stay behind, they say,<note place="foot">The double <term xml:lang="ta">eṉpa</term> seems to me a poetic way of expressing the inevitability of fate - it will happen as they say. T.V.G., however, wants to take HIM as the subject of the first, and read the second as expletive.</note> bearing the affliction we suffer.</l>
    </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
